  "why": "The paper links discovered failures to model internals and statistical failure patterns: it constructs an abstract MDP of RNN internal states, defines state-/transition-level coverage, and empirically shows a correlation between state-coverage / state-variation (Jaccard index) and erroneous behavior (WER). This provides partial diagnostic insight (i.e., failures occur when tests exercise different/less-similar abstract states and transitions). However, the paper does not explain root causes in terms of underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., reliance on spurious/non-robust features, dataset bias, or overfitting) or prescribe targeted mitigations; the analysis stops at correlation between internal-state coverage and errors rather than causal attribution to specific model weaknesses.",
